t stake in the competition for votes. He talks to insiders about their communication practices and strategies, and reflects upon the grand narratives and small opportunistic moments brought before the Canadian public when power is up for grabs. A vivid, first-hand account of campaign strategizing, Inside the NDP War Room offers insights into the NDP breakthroughs of 2011, the full meaning of Quebec's "orange wave," and the future of a party preparing for a new reality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCampaign management -- Canada -- Case studies. 0aCanada. -- Parliament -- Elections, 2006 -- Case studies. 0aCommunication in politics -- Canada -- Case studies. 0aNew Democratic Party -- Case studies. 0aPolitical campaigns -- Canada -- Case studies. 0aPublic relations and politics -- Canada -- Case studies. 0aTruthfulness and falsehood -- Political aspects -- Canada -- Case studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Poverty & Homelessness.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012z978311127413308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012z978311127716540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358784740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773587847423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773587847/original  a978-3-11-127413-3  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012b2012  a978-3-11-127716-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012b2012  aGBV-deGruyter-alles